subject: p18487334
History: Year old man with cauda equine, altered mental status. // intubated, ETT.
Impression: In comparison to chest radiograph, support and monitoring devices are unchanged in position. Mild cardiomegaly is accompanied by pulmonary vascular congestion. Patchy bibasilar opacities likely reflect atelectasis, but aspiration and developing infectious pneumonia are additional considerations.
